    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The Rice algorithm  is simple and very fast It requires only enough memory to hold a single block of 16 or 32 pixels at a time. It codes the pixels in small blocks and so is able to adapt very quickly to changes in the input image statistics (e.g., Rice has no problem handling cosmic rays, bright stars, saturated pixels, etc.)."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
